<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Engine Electrical - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="4">
            <title>Valve Cover Gasket with Pass-Through Connectors</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle,
                        disconnect the main negative battery terminal before removing or installing any electrical
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, make sure the key is in the OFF position before unplugging the
                        connector or relay for the ECM, IDM, and EGR drive module. Failure to turn the key to the OFF
                        position will cause a voltage spike and damage the electrical components.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not tug on any wiring harnesses while trying to remove them. If
                        resistance is felt, find the source of resistance and free up any connectors or clips that are
                        caught before proceeding.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651149" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH11/H11051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Injector connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve cover harness by connecting harness to the high-pressure oil
                    manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install valve cover gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect (6) injectors connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651150" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH09/H09034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Connecting the ICP sensor</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the ICP sensor connector to the valve cover gasket connection.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651151" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH09/H09036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Connecting the BCP sensor</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the BCP sensor connector to the valve cover gasket connection.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651152" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH09/H09035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Connecting brake shutoff valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the brake shutoff valve connector to the valve cover gasket connection.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When removing, disconnecting, or installing the brake shutoff valve, ICP and BCP sensors, the
                        valve cover must be removed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
